Text.string: Hey! I need some help!
Not like I'm goin' anywhere.
“After the war, the COV will maintain control over the following districts: Seaport, Mercutio, Garden District.”
You underestimated the Atlas resistance. We want a thousand more dropships now.
A thousand? Can your idiot followers even FLY ships? I'm still shocked they know how to use their own opposable thumbs.
As it happens, that's one of their favorite snacks, too.
I've got a personal request. I've heard that your holiness makes rather... lifelike statues. I'd like to commission a few.
Tyreen's husks, you mean?
Yeah, that. See, a few of my siblings fled after I assumed control. It'd be so nice to have a family reunion.
Of course. Family is everything.

Just put your signature there and... we are allies! When this war's over, I'll throw in a party on the Zanara—that's my pleasure yacht. I'll let you know when we have the Vault Key. Make sure you fulfill your part of the contract, or I'll liquidate your family!
Whatever. We'll see whose family lasts longer, you trust-fund tyrant.
Help me end this war.
Have an awesome war!
Hnh... that's good dirt, but not end-the-alliance good. Let's try to hack the system and see if we can dig up some more.
Whoa, woozy... Right. Password, uh, one sec. Try “Zanara1234”.
Hello, Mr. Katagawa. Input password.
There's the dirt. Well, ngh, let's have a listen.
Incorrect. Password reminder: Hate, sibling.
Crap. Oh, right. Yeah. “naokomustdiepainfully”—lower case, all one word.
Password accepted. Opening personal data cache thirty-five.
Nice! Once we upload that last data cache to Atlas, my mission will be complete. Then I'm gonna die.
Okay, so now that the contract's signed, I just gotta ask: classy duo like you, how do you stand commanding what is very likely the dumbest army in, well, history?

Don't let the uniform fool you. I'm an undercover Atlas agent. My team was chasing some high-value intel, but... the mission went sour. I managed to get out... just barely. But Atlas Soldiers never die! Though I definitely will. Very soon. AFTER I complete my mission. You can call me Gonner, Gonner Maleggies. Heh. Gallows humor. Now, look around for my agents. They couldn't have have made it far.
Eh, they get the job done.
Hard to beat a mobile food source that obeys your every request.
Intel's getting better, but it sounds like Maliwan's onto us. Defend yourself while the intel uploads!
Nice kills! Resuming download! We're almost done. Hold tight, soldier!
Sure, sure, but come on—they're a bunch of unwashed savages. Ever think of incorporating? Joining the big leagues?
Our army pays us for the privilege of dying... for us. Heh. Who would you say has the better deal?
Damn, m-more security. This is getting good. Wish I had some popcorn. You know, last meal, all that.
Looks like my agent coughed up the intel. Check that locker—dirt might still be around.
Right, but, let's be real. I mean, they're disgusting. How do you stomach even looking at them? I saw one the other day wearing a necklace of some kind of tongues.
Yeah, skag tongues. They're all the rage with the kids these days, apparently.
FYI, my agents probably swallowed the data drives if they were caught. Standard protocol. Extraction might be... difficult.

You're so naive. My family, they fight for me. They sacrifice themselves for me. They fight for my love. That's where you've got it wrong. Family is the most powerful force in this universe, if... you use it right.
Wow. Okay, hit that console and we'll send the intel to HQ.
We'll broadcast that intel throughout the city. Might be enough to turn the tide. What's... that... light?
Whoa, almost forgot!||—Your... reward...
Mission... complete... hrgrhrghlrlrlrhhhh...
The intel we're chasing, it's a secret recording of Katagawa and the Calypsos. Hope it's worth it.
Crap. Rrgh—search the body. We need that intel.
Another one down. Damn. They tore my agent apart limb by limb. Search him.
Nice work. Keep going.
Not there? Damn. Look around. That intel's gotta be close.
Head to the data center. That was supposed to be my job, but... No excuses. I don't have a leg to stand on... Ngh. Whatever.
Data uploading to remote server.
Hey, what the hell?
Crap, alarms. Neutralize that bastard!
Hell yeah, the locker key. Grab it.
I'd bet an arm and a leg that's the key to the locker. You know what I mean.
Interesting. I wonder if Katagawa has dirt on the Calypsos. We could release it and fracture their alliance with Maliwan, maybe give Atlas a leg up!||—Which is one more leg than I have, I guess.
Nice. Let's review the intel.
Intruder! Let's get 'em!
Yeah, you've got this. Kill that Vault Hunter!
I'll be back here! In case they try to flank us!
Easyyyy, hey, hey, I'm on your side! You're here for the intel, right? It's all yours.
Here we go. This dirt better be good. We've got a war to win.
All right, not bad. But we need more.
The data center. Hit that console.
Here we go!
Now I suggest you run along and find the Vault Key before I get hungry... Junior.
Just a few more parts of the contract to go over. Clause 27: “Maliwan will receive exclusive rights to all Eridian technology found in the Vault.”
We're under attack—requesting back up!
We've got ya!
Hell yeah!
Wait a sec, I think I found some hidden intel.
As soon as I win this war, I'm gonna invite those Calypsos to the Zanara and slice off their freakin' heads! And then I'm gonna murder every last one of their stupid followers!
Jackpot, that's the one! Now, let's blast that dirt out and see how the Children of the Vault react.
As soon as I win this war, I'm gonna invite those Calypsos to the Zanara and slice off their freakin' heads! And then I'm gonna murder every last one of their STUPID followers!
(pissed off objections)
He said he's going to murder the God-Queen!
Kill 'em!
Fine with us.
Aw, crap—head's up, we got pissed off bandits incoming! Wipe 'em out!
Hell yeah! It worked! They're fighting each other! Finish 'em off, soldier. Then we'll send that intel to HQ for analysis.
Wonderful, just wonderful. Moving on.
